            "body": "Fixed, hold on let me make the commit :)\r\nEDIT:\r\nThere we go!\r\nhttps://github.com/shirioko/WhatsAPI/commit/23e46afa4eafa608633479cde8569371c222ad4d\r\n\r\nProblem was that the writer object was not reinitialized on reconnect, so it wouldn't restart authentication properly.\r\n\r\nwhatsprot.class.php line 583, function doLogin():\r\n\r\n        $data = $this->_writer->StartStream(WhatsProt::_whatsAppServer, $resource);\r\n        $feat = $this->addFeatures();\r\n        $auth = $this->addAuth();\r\n        $this->sendData($data);\r\n        $this->sendNode($feat);\r\n        $this->sendNode($auth);\r\n\r\n        $this->processInboundData($this->readData());\r\n        $data = $this->addAuthResponse();\r\nStartStream initializes authentication flow using the provided key, in this case from the last connection, and addAuthResponse resets the keys in the reader and writer objects. As you can see StartStream is called before you receive the new key so it will use the old key instead.\r\n\r\nI've made a better fix by resetting the reader and writer keys on login:\r\nhttps://github.com/shirioko/WhatsAPI/commit/9072ba5f7ff51ebc64ee15ab5b3b28c93119e5b8",
